WEBVTT

00:01.436 --> 00:03.264
<i>Previously</i> <i>
on "Resident Alien"...</i>

00:03.307 --> 00:05.092
<i>How could I not remember?</i>

00:05.135 --> 00:06.745
<i>When people experience</i> <i>
a loss of time,</i>

00:06.789 --> 00:09.009
<i>it's often because they've</i> <i>
been abducted by aliens.</i>

00:09.052 --> 00:10.401
<i>I'm an alien.</i>

00:10.445 --> 00:12.403
<i>We are very good</i> <i>
at changing people's memories.</i>

00:12.447 --> 00:15.580
FBI. The murderer is
not Harry Vanderspeigle.

00:15.624 --> 00:17.626
Guess what--you're not
getting your ball back.

00:17.669 --> 00:19.976
I've hidden it where
you'll never find it.

00:20.020 --> 00:21.282
Abigail Hodges,
you're under arrest

00:21.325 --> 00:22.848
for the murder of Sam Hodges.

00:22.892 --> 00:25.025
<i>I have built a radio.</i>

00:25.068 --> 00:26.504
<i>The signal will tell my people</i>

00:26.548 --> 00:29.899
<i>not to come</i> <i>
and kill everyone...</i>

00:29.942 --> 00:31.161
for 50 years.

00:31.205 --> 00:34.817
- We need to stop it!
- No!

00:34.860 --> 00:36.253
It's receiving a signal.

00:36.297 --> 00:39.778
It's a phone number
from New York City.

00:39.822 --> 00:41.693
Sunny went into labor
all of a sudden.

00:41.737 --> 00:45.567
- I can fix it.
- Let the doctor do his job.

00:45.610 --> 00:47.743
<i>I've held a lot of babies</i> <i>
since Jay was born.</i>

00:47.786 --> 00:52.139
I understand now
why you feel guilty.

00:53.183 --> 00:56.143
[siren wailing]

00:56.186 --> 00:59.146
<i>[intense music]</i>

00:59.189 --> 01:02.192
<i>♪</i>

01:02.236 --> 01:05.413
[tires screeching]
- Go after him.

01:05.456 --> 01:07.067
Flush him out. I'll meet you
on the other side.

01:07.110 --> 01:08.242
I got it.

01:08.285 --> 01:11.114
Police, drop the weapon!
[gunshot]

01:11.158 --> 01:12.724
Shit.

01:12.768 --> 01:15.075
Dispatch, this is unit 92.
I got shots fired.

01:15.118 --> 01:16.685
Need backup at my location.

01:16.728 --> 01:19.166
Jesse! Jesse! <i>
- Copy that.</i>

01:19.209 --> 01:20.645
<i>Backup en route.</i>

01:20.689 --> 01:24.997
Jesse?

01:25.041 --> 01:28.131
[sirens wailing]

01:30.438 --> 01:32.266
<i>[echoing]</i> <i>
I got an officer down.</i>

01:32.309 --> 01:35.312
<i>[indistinct chatter</i> <i>
over police radio]</i>

01:38.228 --> 01:40.143
[knocking at door]

01:40.187 --> 01:43.059
Mike. <i>
[TV playing indistinctly]</i>

01:43.103 --> 01:44.582
[knocking continues]

01:44.626 --> 01:46.671
Come on, man,
I know you're in there.

01:51.633 --> 01:54.462
- Bill, I can't do that, man.
- [sighs]

01:54.505 --> 01:58.074
Mike, you're the only one
he would have trusted with him.

01:58.118 --> 02:01.251
<i>[somber music]</i>

02:01.295 --> 02:05.995
<i>♪</i>

02:06.038 --> 02:08.780
[puppy whimpers]
- [sighs]

02:08.824 --> 02:10.434
You take care
of yourself, okay?

02:10.478 --> 02:12.871
Thanks.
Thanks, man.

02:15.178 --> 02:17.441
[sighs]

02:17.485 --> 02:20.140
[sniffles]
I miss him, too, Cletus.

02:20.183 --> 02:22.011
- [whimpers]
- [sniffles]

02:22.054 --> 02:24.274
Welcome to your new home.

02:24.318 --> 02:27.669
<i>[laidback acoustic strumming]</i>

02:27.712 --> 02:34.719
<i>♪</i>

02:34.763 --> 02:37.635
<i>1,900 miles--</i>

02:37.679 --> 02:40.551
<i>that's how close</i> <i>
I am to New York City,</i>

02:40.595 --> 02:42.640
<i>to one of my people.</i>

02:42.684 --> 02:45.948
<i>1,900 miles from standing</i> <i>
in front of a being</i>

02:45.991 --> 02:47.471
<i>who knows what I know...</i>

02:47.515 --> 02:50.866
<i>who has stood in the ice wind</i> <i>
desert as a child.</i>

02:50.909 --> 02:53.216
<i>I am different now.</i>

02:53.260 --> 02:54.957
<i>Asta knows this version of me,</i>

02:55.000 --> 02:58.352
<i>but I am 1,900 miles</i> <i>
from being with someone</i>

02:58.395 --> 03:00.789
<i>who knows</i> <i>
the alien part of me--</i>

03:00.832 --> 03:02.965
<i>the real me.</i>

03:03.008 --> 03:05.707
<i>[Dana Sipos' "Hoodoo"]</i>

03:05.750 --> 03:08.405
<i>So why can I not dial</i> <i>
this number?</i>

03:09.972 --> 03:13.410
<i>♪ Hoodoos</i>

03:13.454 --> 03:15.543
<i>♪</i>

03:15.586 --> 03:19.721
<i>♪ Do not take their shape</i> <i>
for you ♪</i>

03:19.764 --> 03:24.116
<i>♪ Trace your eye</i> <i>
down their rocky spire ♪</i>

03:24.160 --> 03:28.251
<i>♪ Laced with limestone</i> <i>
and wind and fire ♪</i>

03:28.295 --> 03:30.035
<i>♪</i>

03:30.079 --> 03:32.037
- Hey.
- Oh.

03:32.081 --> 03:33.256
Hey.

03:33.300 --> 03:35.563
<i>♪</i>

03:35.606 --> 03:37.782
It was nice to talk
to you last night.

03:39.393 --> 03:41.482
Kind of felt like
old times again.

03:41.525 --> 03:43.353
What?
- Oh.

03:43.397 --> 03:45.094
W-what--what
are you upset about?

03:45.137 --> 03:47.488
Nothing happened.
All we did was talk about Jay.

03:47.531 --> 03:49.533
- Yeah, I know.
- Asta.

03:49.577 --> 03:51.927
- I shouldn't have come here.
- I did--

03:53.537 --> 03:56.758
Please, you don't have to go.
- Yes, I do.

03:56.801 --> 04:00.109
<i>♪ It lives</i> <i>
in a fistful of sky ♪</i>

04:00.152 --> 04:06.289
<i>♪ Just beyond your reach</i>

04:06.333 --> 04:08.596
<i>♪</i>

04:08.639 --> 04:11.294
Nice seeing you
at Laurant's last night.

04:11.338 --> 04:13.992
Mm, mm.

04:22.262 --> 04:24.655
I saw you left
pretty quickly.

04:26.440 --> 04:27.919
You know,
if there's ever anything

04:27.963 --> 04:29.660
you want to talk about,
like, no big deal,

04:29.704 --> 04:31.749
but you can talk to me.

04:33.795 --> 04:37.102
[sighs]
Thank you, Deputy.

04:37.146 --> 04:39.235
Now that you mention it,

04:39.279 --> 04:41.368
I'd like to know what
you've been scribbling down

04:41.411 --> 04:42.760
in your little notebook there.

04:42.804 --> 04:45.415
You doing another
solo investigation?

04:47.330 --> 04:49.593
Do you remember my dress you
picked up from the cleaners?

04:49.637 --> 04:52.161
The one I don't remember
dropping off?

04:52.204 --> 04:53.336
And what dress
you talking about?

04:53.380 --> 04:54.859
You talking
about that green dress,

04:54.903 --> 04:56.470
or you talking about that
dress you talk about every day

04:56.513 --> 04:57.993
like it's some kind
of government conspiracy?

04:58.036 --> 05:00.865
- You have to admit it's weird.
- [sighs]

05:00.909 --> 05:03.912
Basically
the whole day is a blank.

05:03.955 --> 05:05.566
Do you remember it?
- I mean, no.

05:05.609 --> 05:07.089
But I can't remember what I had
for breakfast this morning.

05:07.132 --> 05:08.830
You know, ask me
what color socks I'm wearing.

05:08.873 --> 05:11.789
What color socks
are you wearing?

05:11.833 --> 05:13.400
Well, actually,
I'm wearing black socks

05:13.443 --> 05:14.836
'cause that's all I own--
is black socks.

05:14.879 --> 05:16.446
But if I did own socks
that was a different color,

05:16.490 --> 05:18.143
I wouldn't remember
what color I was wearing.

05:18.187 --> 05:19.319
You know why?
It don't matter.

05:19.362 --> 05:22.060
Sir, you might want to look
at this.

05:23.671 --> 05:26.500
What the hell she doing?
That's Miss Taylor bike.

05:26.543 --> 05:30.112
Oh, shit. Hell, no.
Hell, no!

05:30.155 --> 05:32.854
Hey, get off that bike!
Get off that damn bike!

05:32.897 --> 05:34.464
That ain't your bike.
- Come on, Sheriff!

05:34.508 --> 05:36.771
Hey, I can outrun that bike!

05:38.207 --> 05:40.383
Ellen?

05:40.427 --> 05:43.517
[object rolling]

05:43.560 --> 05:44.822
Hey, Ellen,
can you cover for me?

05:44.866 --> 05:46.433
I got to take care
of something.

05:46.476 --> 05:47.999
- Sure.
- Okay. Thanks.

05:48.043 --> 05:48.957
I won't be long.

05:56.138 --> 05:57.269
Close call.
[sighs]

05:57.313 --> 05:58.662
Almost as close as you were

05:58.706 --> 06:01.012
to getting your eye poked out
by a tree.

06:01.056 --> 06:04.842
In my defense, I had just
had dinner with my parents.

06:04.886 --> 06:07.454
Also, that tree
was waving pretty wildly.

06:07.497 --> 06:10.370
Listen,
as a medical professional,

06:10.413 --> 06:13.024
I suggest you drink
a little less.

06:13.068 --> 06:17.028
But as a single bitch
living in this dead-ass town,

06:17.072 --> 06:19.944
I suggest you invite me out
next time.

06:19.988 --> 06:21.511
Wow.

06:21.555 --> 06:22.730
All right.

06:22.773 --> 06:25.254
- Yeah, there's more of that.
- Okay.

06:25.297 --> 06:28.213
<i>[quirky music]</i>

06:28.257 --> 06:29.780
<i>♪</i>

06:29.824 --> 06:32.653
What do you mean you got
a phone number from an alien?

06:32.696 --> 06:34.785
Why didn't you tell me sooner?
What did they say?

06:34.829 --> 06:38.223
Well, I did not call.
It might be a trap.

06:38.267 --> 06:40.008
<i>It's not a trap.</i>

06:40.051 --> 06:41.749
If you worried more
about traps,

06:41.792 --> 06:43.925
then you would still be
in the ocean

06:43.968 --> 06:47.668
instead of in a box of water
in the mountains. [laughs]

06:47.711 --> 06:49.974
Does this thing have to keep
popping into my head?

06:50.018 --> 06:51.454
<i>You think I like it</i> <i>
in there?</i>

06:51.498 --> 06:53.151
<i>It's darker than the woods</i> <i>
in a Tim Burton movie.</i>

06:53.195 --> 06:55.066
You shut the hell up
about what's in my head

06:55.110 --> 06:57.199
and stop putting the TV on
in front of this thing.

06:57.242 --> 06:58.940
<i>He's not calling</i>

06:58.983 --> 07:01.595
<i>because he's afraid</i> <i>
his people will reject him.</i>

07:01.638 --> 07:03.248
<i>He's worried he's too human.</i>

07:03.292 --> 07:04.772
That is a lie!

07:04.815 --> 07:07.905
Liars do not get food. <i>
- I'm kidding.</i>

07:07.949 --> 07:09.646
<i>Can't you take a joke?</i> <i>
It's obviously a trap.</i>

07:09.690 --> 07:11.561
Good octopus.

07:11.605 --> 07:13.650
Okay. We don't have
any other leads.

07:13.694 --> 07:16.348
And if we don't do anything,
everyone is going to die.

07:16.392 --> 07:19.090
So, if you don't call
that phone number, I will.

07:19.134 --> 07:20.570
Fine.

07:21.571 --> 07:23.747
Okay.

07:23.791 --> 07:25.227
<i>[line trilling]</i>
- Mm.

07:25.270 --> 07:27.098
<i>[line clicks,</i> <i>
person speaks indistinctly]</i>

07:27.142 --> 07:29.579
Hello. Can I talk
to the alien, please?

07:29.623 --> 07:32.495
<i>[person speaks indistinctly]</i>
Mm.

07:32.539 --> 07:34.715
He hung up.

07:34.758 --> 07:37.195
He knows my mother.

07:37.239 --> 07:38.980
And they had intercourse.

07:40.721 --> 07:43.071
Demelio's Pizzeria,
East Third Street.

07:43.114 --> 07:45.508
Pack your bags.
We're going to New York.

07:45.552 --> 07:48.598
<i>I cannot go to New York.</i> <i>
The octopus is right.</i>

07:48.642 --> 07:50.818
<i>I have changed.</i> <i>
I am too human.</i>

07:50.861 --> 07:52.776
<i>What if the alien</i> <i>
will not help me?</i>

07:52.820 --> 07:54.735
<i>I heard that.</i> <i>
He just admitted it.</i>

07:54.778 --> 07:56.780
Get out of my head.

07:56.824 --> 07:59.522
[cell phone ringing]

07:59.566 --> 08:02.046
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

08:02.090 --> 08:04.309
Well, answer it.
It might be them.

08:04.353 --> 08:07.138
<i>♪</i>

08:07.182 --> 08:08.183
Hello?

08:08.226 --> 08:10.446
Morning, Doc.
It's the Sheriff.

08:10.490 --> 08:12.535
[elevator bell dings]

08:16.104 --> 08:17.322
Hi, Dad.

08:17.366 --> 08:20.021
- [grunts]
- [scoffs]

08:26.244 --> 08:28.682
<i>This is weird--</i> <i>
she looks like me,</i>

08:28.725 --> 08:30.684
<i>if I fell face-first</i> <i>
into a pile of metal.</i>

08:30.727 --> 08:31.902
At first,
I thought she was just

08:31.946 --> 08:33.600
some hippie drifter
from Boulder,

08:33.643 --> 08:36.777
but, uh, then she showed me
this right here.

08:38.387 --> 08:39.910
[groans]

08:42.217 --> 08:44.436
I remember this.

08:44.480 --> 08:46.830
This was the day
she sat on my knee,

08:46.874 --> 08:48.440
and we looked at the camera,

08:48.484 --> 08:50.007
and that person took
our photograph.

08:50.051 --> 08:53.358
Yes, the daughter you've been
telling me so much about,

08:53.402 --> 08:55.012
from your first wife
before Isabelle,

08:55.056 --> 08:57.188
and her name is...

08:57.232 --> 08:59.495
right on the tip of my tongue.

09:02.629 --> 09:04.718
Um, I think she said Liza.

09:04.761 --> 09:07.242
Liza is her name.

09:07.285 --> 09:09.244
- Liza is her name.
- Mm-hmm.

09:09.287 --> 09:11.507
I'm very fertile.

09:11.551 --> 09:14.902
This is my sweet little girl.

09:14.945 --> 09:17.078
Well, we caught
your sweet little girl

09:17.121 --> 09:18.296
trying to steal a bike.

09:18.340 --> 09:19.733
It turns out she's got a record

09:19.776 --> 09:21.648
for shoplifting
in, uh, New Mexico.

09:21.691 --> 09:24.433
Her mama sent her to a camp
for troubled teens,

09:24.476 --> 09:26.653
but she ran away
'cause she's troubled.

09:26.696 --> 09:29.307
She also pulled my hair.

09:29.351 --> 09:31.788
It didn't hurt, though.
I have strong roots.

09:31.832 --> 09:33.747
Are you even aware
of what's going on

09:33.790 --> 09:35.226
with your daughter, Doc?
- Yes.

09:35.270 --> 09:39.361
Thank you for arresting her
and throwing her in jail.

09:39.404 --> 09:41.537
Well, hold on--I don't think
there's any need for that,

09:41.581 --> 09:42.973
at least not yet.

09:43.017 --> 09:44.801
I'm all right with releasing
her into your custody.

09:44.845 --> 09:48.588
No, you throw her in jail.

09:48.631 --> 09:51.373
[laughing awkwardly]
He's joking.

09:51.416 --> 09:54.158
He'll take her home.

09:54.202 --> 09:57.292
<i>Is this how humans feel</i> <i>
when they have a child--</i>

09:57.335 --> 10:01.470
<i>angry and resentful for having</i> <i>
to care for a tiny thing?</i>

10:01.513 --> 10:03.167
<i>If she were a pet bird,</i>

10:03.211 --> 10:05.648
<i>I would leave</i> <i>
the cage door open</i>

10:05.692 --> 10:07.955
<i>and the ceiling fan on.</i>

10:07.998 --> 10:12.089
So, Liza, boot camp, huh?
Why were you sent there?

10:12.133 --> 10:14.309
- Murder.
- Cool.

10:14.352 --> 10:16.659
Maybe we should call your mom,
have her come pick you up.

10:16.703 --> 10:18.530
Good luck--
my mom is in Italy right now,

10:18.574 --> 10:20.924
getting fingered on a Vespa.

10:20.968 --> 10:22.230
Good talk.

10:22.273 --> 10:26.974
It's a bad--it's a bad talk.
That was bad.

10:27.017 --> 10:29.541
Why are you acting so weird?

10:29.585 --> 10:32.544
Wait, are you high?

10:32.588 --> 10:34.503
Yes.

10:34.546 --> 10:37.245
Yes, he is. Ugh.

10:37.288 --> 10:39.682
It's legal in Colorado.

10:39.726 --> 10:42.642
Do not bum my stone, man.

10:42.685 --> 10:44.600
Go home to your mother.

10:44.644 --> 10:47.211
Asta will take you
to the airport.

10:47.255 --> 10:48.691
That was quick.

10:48.735 --> 10:50.040
You usually at least pretend

10:50.084 --> 10:52.695
for a few days
before you tell me to leave.

10:52.739 --> 10:55.089
I'll make it real easy for you.
Have a nice life.

10:55.132 --> 10:58.135
Okay, I will.

10:58.179 --> 11:00.660
Where is the bacon lady?
[door opens, bells jingle]

11:00.703 --> 11:03.184
- You can't just let her leave.
- Mm?

11:03.227 --> 11:04.489
She wants to go.

11:04.533 --> 11:07.841
She wants her father.
We have to help her.

11:07.884 --> 11:10.017
An hour ago,
you wanted to go to New York

11:10.060 --> 11:12.236
to save the rest of the humans.

11:12.280 --> 11:13.760
You are flip-floppy.

11:13.803 --> 11:15.849
She happens to be
one of those humans.

11:15.892 --> 11:18.286
You killed her father,

11:18.329 --> 11:21.245
so we are staying here
until we get her safely home.

11:24.901 --> 11:26.816
She does not need our help.

11:26.860 --> 11:29.384
She's already making friends.

11:29.427 --> 11:30.907
Shit.

11:32.648 --> 11:34.302
I think
we can make that happen, yeah.

11:34.345 --> 11:35.782
You ever been on one before?
- Oh, yes.

11:35.825 --> 11:37.479
Let's do this thing.

11:37.522 --> 11:39.655
- Hey, nice bike.
- Thanks.

11:39.699 --> 11:41.135
I had the same one
in high school.

11:41.178 --> 11:43.964
She's 16,
so get the hell out of here.

11:45.661 --> 11:47.228
Faster.

11:47.271 --> 11:50.231
[engine turning over]

11:50.274 --> 11:51.580
You're not my mother.

11:51.623 --> 11:52.886
I know.
She's doing the Vespa thing.

11:52.929 --> 11:55.062
Look, I want to help you.

11:55.105 --> 11:56.977
Because you're
my dad's newest sex toy?

11:57.020 --> 11:59.719
Oh, my God, knock it off.
We just work together.

11:59.762 --> 12:02.243
Yeah, you're
a little too old for him.

12:02.286 --> 12:05.246
Look, my mom left me
when I was a baby,

12:05.289 --> 12:08.423
so I know a few things
about being abandoned.

12:08.466 --> 12:10.033
So now I'm your therapist?

12:10.077 --> 12:12.296
- You know what? Eat shit.
- [chuckles]

12:12.340 --> 12:13.689
Yeah. Laugh it off.

12:13.733 --> 12:15.909
And have a little pity party
while you're at it.

12:15.952 --> 12:17.780
I'm not going to let you get
on a motorcycle

12:17.824 --> 12:21.001
and get beat up
by some asshole biker, okay?

12:24.352 --> 12:27.311
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

12:27.355 --> 12:33.274
<i>♪</i>

12:33.317 --> 12:35.842
Did you really used to have
that motorcycle?

12:35.885 --> 12:38.845
No, my asshole
biker boyfriend did.

12:38.888 --> 12:43.588
<i>♪</i>

12:43.632 --> 12:47.157
I don't think my mom
even wanted to go to Italy.

12:47.201 --> 12:50.378
I think she just needed
an excuse to ship me off.

12:53.468 --> 12:55.818
I figured...

12:55.862 --> 12:58.038
I hadn't seen
my dad in a while.

12:59.953 --> 13:02.433
I was just borrowing that bike
to get to the cabin.

13:02.477 --> 13:04.740
I'm not a thief.

13:04.784 --> 13:07.090
Not really.

13:07.134 --> 13:09.701
I mean,
I do steal a lot of shit.

13:09.745 --> 13:12.269
[giggles]

13:15.011 --> 13:17.231
Something's different.

13:18.841 --> 13:21.888
At least he used to go through
the motions of being a father.

13:21.931 --> 13:25.239
Yeah, well...

13:25.282 --> 13:28.633
he's not the same man
you used to know.

13:28.677 --> 13:30.897
Maybe just give him a chance.

13:34.770 --> 13:38.730
I really miss you,
Aunt Cathy.

13:38.774 --> 13:40.776
You were the only one
I ever told

13:40.820 --> 13:43.344
about the UFO I saw
when I was a kid...

13:43.387 --> 13:44.562
except John.

13:44.606 --> 13:48.436
He thinks I'm crazy
but loves me anyway.

13:50.612 --> 13:52.832
God, I really hope
you can hear me.

13:52.875 --> 13:55.443
Aunt Cathy,
if you're listening,

13:55.486 --> 13:57.401
please give me a sign.

13:57.445 --> 13:58.968
- Liv!
- Oh!

13:59.012 --> 14:01.014
- Hey, Liv.
- Hey.

14:01.057 --> 14:02.363
Just bringing Max by.

14:02.406 --> 14:04.713
His first father-son trip
to the cemetery.

14:04.756 --> 14:06.889
- What is that tall thing?
- Ah.

14:06.933 --> 14:09.849
That is a monument
honoring the 59.

14:09.892 --> 14:11.372
The star on top represents

14:11.415 --> 14:13.765
the man that they went back
to save.

14:13.809 --> 14:15.419
It's more than a monument.

14:15.463 --> 14:18.031
They're all actually buried
under there.

14:18.074 --> 14:20.250
It's a mass grave
kind of thing.

14:20.294 --> 14:22.339
Awesome.

14:22.383 --> 14:25.081
Really? Huh.

14:25.125 --> 14:27.388
Well, uh, you'll be happy
to hear this year

14:27.431 --> 14:30.173
at Patience Family Day
the theme is "Remember When."

14:30.217 --> 14:33.916
So we'll be honoring the 59--
Max stop digging.

14:33.960 --> 14:35.918
I'm trying to rebrand
the whole narrative,

14:35.962 --> 14:37.746
you know,
just remind people that

14:37.789 --> 14:39.922
these aren't just 59 dead men.

14:39.966 --> 14:41.706
You know,
these are--these are heroes.

14:41.750 --> 14:43.099
Mm, that sounds great.

14:43.143 --> 14:44.753
Yeah. We're going to have
mining-themed games.

14:44.796 --> 14:46.233
Kids are putting on a play

14:46.276 --> 14:47.974
written by yours truly.
- Ah.

14:48.017 --> 14:49.932
Hey, maybe even get
real authentic--

14:49.976 --> 14:51.586
swap out the toilet paper
in the porta-potties

14:51.629 --> 14:54.197
for corn husks.
- Yeah, maybe not that one.

14:54.241 --> 14:55.416
Ah, I already
started shucking.

14:55.459 --> 14:57.418
Well, uh, good to see you.
- Yeah.

14:57.461 --> 14:58.898
Okay. Come on, Max.

14:58.941 --> 15:01.857
Hey, Max, I've been meaning
to ask you something.

15:01.901 --> 15:03.598
You know that sketch
you had me do--

15:03.641 --> 15:05.034
the--the one of the alien?

15:05.078 --> 15:09.343
Oh, um...
yeah, I made all that stuff up.

15:09.386 --> 15:10.648
Aliens aren't real.

15:10.692 --> 15:17.829
<i>♪</i>

15:22.182 --> 15:24.619
Well, it looks like
she's been here before.

15:24.662 --> 15:26.099
Nice talking with you.

15:26.142 --> 15:28.797
This is a bad idea.
I do not like children.

15:28.840 --> 15:30.190
Yes, you do.

15:30.233 --> 15:31.887
I saw the way
you looked at Sunny's baby.

15:31.931 --> 15:34.890
That is different.
A baby is tiny.

15:34.934 --> 15:36.283
And it doesn't speak.

15:36.326 --> 15:38.633
Well, every baby grows
into a Liza.

15:38.676 --> 15:40.548
Then why do you feed them?

15:40.591 --> 15:43.986
'Cause if you don't,
they will die.

15:44.030 --> 15:46.554
No, mm-mm.
Don't even think about it.

15:46.597 --> 15:48.164
Anything happens to her
or if she leaves,

15:48.208 --> 15:49.818
we will have
much bigger problems.

15:49.861 --> 15:52.299
Okay, keep her alive and happy

15:52.342 --> 15:54.170
until her mom comes home
in a few days

15:54.214 --> 15:57.217
and we go to New York
and save humanity.

15:59.001 --> 16:02.396
Also, try to act
as normal as possible

16:02.439 --> 16:04.920
and keep the door
to your alien bunker locked

16:04.964 --> 16:07.401
and the talking octopus
in your room.

16:09.055 --> 16:10.230
<i>I have got this.</i>

16:10.273 --> 16:12.275
<i>I can be a good father.</i>

16:12.319 --> 16:14.147
<i>I've seen</i> <i>
a lot of television.</i>

16:14.190 --> 16:16.410
Ugh, what happened
to the Wi-Fi?

16:16.453 --> 16:18.194
And it smells like
dead people up here.

16:18.238 --> 16:21.981
Then you should take
a shower...

16:22.024 --> 16:23.634
my darling daughter.

16:27.247 --> 16:31.033
<i>[steady country music]</i>

16:31.077 --> 16:34.297
<i>♪ Adiós, mi amigo, adiós</i>

16:34.341 --> 16:36.299
Hey, hey, hey!

16:36.343 --> 16:41.304
<i>♪</i>

16:44.742 --> 16:46.962
Buddy, you took my spot.

16:48.137 --> 16:49.660
Glad to see
you got a new truck.

16:49.704 --> 16:52.141
It was the, uh, problem
with the emergency brake

16:52.185 --> 16:53.969
on the last one, right?
- Oh, you're real funny.

16:54.013 --> 16:55.449
You could have killed someone.

16:55.492 --> 16:57.059
Now you're pretending
to care about other people.

16:57.103 --> 17:00.280
Hey, maybe show me how much
you care with your fist.

17:00.323 --> 17:01.977
That's you do things, right?

17:02.021 --> 17:03.413
Looks like you already lost
one fight today.

17:03.457 --> 17:05.285
But keep playing with me,
and we'll make it two.

17:05.328 --> 17:07.026
It would be the honor
of my life

17:07.069 --> 17:08.636
to lay your ass out.

17:08.679 --> 17:10.594
In fact, I'll do it twice--
once for me, once for Asta.

17:10.638 --> 17:11.769
Well, if she's so upset,

17:11.813 --> 17:14.033
why did she stay
at my house last night?

17:15.338 --> 17:16.557
Mm.

17:16.600 --> 17:18.211
Bullshit.

17:22.737 --> 17:25.435
[engine turning over, revs]

17:25.479 --> 17:27.698
<i>[light music]</i>

17:27.742 --> 17:30.049
Yeah, good to see you.
[door opens, bells jingle]

17:31.572 --> 17:33.052
Hey, hey.

17:34.705 --> 17:36.011
Got some good news.

17:36.055 --> 17:38.013
Oh, yeah,
the Nats won four in a row.

17:38.057 --> 17:39.667
I'm not talking
about the Nationals.

17:39.710 --> 17:42.104
My biopsy came back negative.

17:42.148 --> 17:43.845
Biopsy? What biopsy?

17:43.888 --> 17:45.238
You're the one
who kept nagging me

17:45.281 --> 17:46.630
to get my mole checked.

17:46.674 --> 17:48.197
You drove me to the clinic.

17:48.241 --> 17:50.460
[scoffs]
What? When?

17:50.504 --> 17:52.201
Two weeks ago.

17:52.245 --> 17:54.290
Well, obviously you didn't
tell me it was for a biopsy,

17:54.334 --> 17:55.639
or I would have remembered.

17:55.683 --> 17:58.294
Of course I told you.

17:58.338 --> 18:01.689
You ain't been
the same since D.C.

18:01.732 --> 18:03.038
You got to deal with that.

18:03.082 --> 18:05.040
See a doctor, psychiatrist,

18:05.084 --> 18:06.650
hell, anybody.
- Mm-hmm.

18:06.694 --> 18:09.175
Tell me, why exactly should
I take mental-health advice

18:09.218 --> 18:11.220
from somebody who stayed
holed up in the house,

18:11.264 --> 18:13.048
refusing to speak to anybody
for six months

18:13.092 --> 18:14.615
when Mama died, huh?
- [sighs]

18:14.658 --> 18:16.834
Yeah, well, I'm not the one
carrying a deadly weapon.

18:16.878 --> 18:18.140
Okay, all right,
you know what?

18:18.184 --> 18:19.968
Is this--is this
what we have now? Is this us?

18:20.011 --> 18:21.796
We just gonna fight
all the time?

18:21.839 --> 18:23.145
I got friends.
They got dads.

18:23.189 --> 18:24.538
They go to games.
They go fishing and shit.

18:24.581 --> 18:26.235
We ain't done nothing like that
since I was a kid.

18:26.279 --> 18:28.237
Instead, all I got
is you sitting across from me

18:28.281 --> 18:30.239
telling me all the things
you think are wrong with me.

18:30.283 --> 18:32.241
You're a young man.

18:32.285 --> 18:34.548
It's not normal
to forget stuff like that.

18:34.591 --> 18:39.640
<i>♪</i>

18:39.683 --> 18:42.599
[jazzy music playing]

18:42.643 --> 18:44.035
♪

18:44.079 --> 18:47.648
- What are we eating?
- [grunts]

18:47.691 --> 18:50.651
This is missing something.
What is it?

18:50.694 --> 18:53.219
Oh, right, flavor.

18:53.262 --> 18:57.353
Have you ever heard of salt
or a-a vegetable maybe?

18:57.397 --> 19:00.008
I did have some vegetables,

19:00.051 --> 19:01.836
but they grew organisms
on them.

19:01.879 --> 19:03.490
You know I can't eat gluten.

19:03.533 --> 19:05.709
Did you forget that, or are you
purposely trying to kill me?

19:05.753 --> 19:07.798
Would gluten kill you?

19:07.842 --> 19:09.931
- I'll just starve.
- Mm.

19:09.974 --> 19:12.325
You need to call my boot camp
and tell them that I'm with you

19:12.368 --> 19:13.935
and I'm too sick to go back.

19:13.978 --> 19:15.893
That would be lying.

19:15.937 --> 19:19.549
Lying is bad, young lady.

19:19.593 --> 19:21.986
I will now discipline you

19:22.030 --> 19:25.555
by sending you to bed
without supper.

19:25.599 --> 19:28.079
<i>♪</i>

19:28.123 --> 19:29.429
I already told you--

19:29.472 --> 19:31.126
I'm not going to eat
your shitty gut-bomb pasta.

19:31.170 --> 19:34.651
Fine. Fine. Fine.

19:34.695 --> 19:37.437
More--more gluten for me.

19:37.480 --> 19:38.786
Enjoy.

19:38.829 --> 19:40.353
I am.

19:41.963 --> 19:45.053
<i>I know you feel</i> <i>
like you're different.</i>

19:45.096 --> 19:47.229
<i>You are different.</i>

19:47.273 --> 19:50.580
<i>You can see what's going on.</i>

19:50.624 --> 19:52.147
<i>Aliens are real.</i>

19:52.191 --> 19:53.714
<i>Hey, uh, Deputy,</i> <i>
where are you?</i>

19:53.757 --> 19:57.413
<i>That car was supposed to be</i> <i>
back an hour ago.</i>

19:57.457 --> 20:00.721
Uh, just at the market
picking up supplies

20:00.764 --> 20:02.418
for the break room. <i>
- Hey, uh, Dep.</i>

20:02.462 --> 20:04.028
You know what?
While you're there,

20:04.072 --> 20:05.204
go ahead and pick me up
a lotto ticket.

20:05.247 --> 20:07.118
<i>Go ahead pick up one</i> <i>
for Cletus, too.</i>

20:07.162 --> 20:08.555
Sure thing, Sheriff.

20:08.598 --> 20:11.035
- You want a lotto ticket?
- [grunts]

20:11.079 --> 20:13.473
[sighs, muttering to self]

20:13.516 --> 20:15.344
You spent the night
at Jimmy's?

20:16.737 --> 20:18.782
- It's not what you think.
- What is wrong with you?

20:18.826 --> 20:20.567
How do you even get
within ten feet of that creep

20:20.610 --> 20:22.743
without ripping his face off?
- Shh.

20:24.701 --> 20:27.269
We had to deliver
my cousin Sunny's baby, okay?

20:27.313 --> 20:29.271
It messed with my head.

20:29.315 --> 20:32.231
Okay, great.
So call your friends.

20:32.274 --> 20:35.321
- You don't understand.
- No, I really don't.

20:35.364 --> 20:37.540
Well, Jimmy does, so it's not
a terrible surprise

20:37.584 --> 20:40.500
that I want to talk to him
about it and not you.

20:40.543 --> 20:42.371
I guess I'm just somebody
who doesn't like watching

20:42.415 --> 20:44.199
their best friend ruin
their life.

20:44.243 --> 20:45.766
Oh, really?

20:45.809 --> 20:48.334
And that's just
something for me to do?

20:48.377 --> 20:49.813
What is that supposed
to mean?

20:49.857 --> 20:51.641
You think I don't know
that you come in here

20:51.685 --> 20:52.729
for hangover IVs?

20:52.773 --> 20:54.165
Sorry, D'arcy.

20:54.209 --> 20:56.298
You want to talk about
watching friends ruin lives?

20:56.342 --> 20:58.344
Let's talk about it.
- You know, it's weird.

20:58.387 --> 21:00.259
You didn't seem worried
about this

21:00.302 --> 21:01.347
until I started helping Jay.

21:01.390 --> 21:03.000
Oh, is that what
you're doing?

21:03.044 --> 21:05.133
You're "helping" her?

21:05.176 --> 21:06.526
Yes.

21:06.569 --> 21:08.789
She needs somebody to talk to.

21:08.832 --> 21:10.530
Maybe she'll listen
to my dating advice.

21:10.573 --> 21:12.532
I'm not so sure
you're the best person

21:12.575 --> 21:14.447
to be giving advice about men.

21:14.490 --> 21:15.839
Wow.

21:15.883 --> 21:17.406
D'arce.

21:17.450 --> 21:18.712
Okay.

21:18.755 --> 21:22.063
[door opens, slams]

21:22.106 --> 21:24.283
<i>[somber music]</i>

21:27.460 --> 21:30.419
<i>[bluesy music]</i>

21:30.463 --> 21:34.336
<i>♪</i>

21:34.380 --> 21:35.859
Where's Murphy?

21:35.903 --> 21:39.646
<i>♪</i>

21:39.689 --> 21:41.517
"If you ever want to see
your dog again,

21:41.561 --> 21:43.824
return my alien ball--Alien."

21:43.867 --> 21:45.782
[scoffs]
It's not even your dog.

21:45.826 --> 21:48.785
We win again.
- No, we don't.

21:48.829 --> 21:50.613
Murphy's my responsibility.

21:50.657 --> 21:52.615
Her owners pay me to walk her.

21:52.659 --> 21:55.139
We have to get her back.

21:55.183 --> 21:57.359
<i>Humans are obsessed</i> <i>
with pets.</i>

21:57.403 --> 22:00.057
<i>If I give Liza</i> <i>
this slobbering lump of fur,</i>

22:00.101 --> 22:03.147
<i>she will become so distracted</i> <i>
taking care of the dog,</i>

22:03.191 --> 22:05.280
<i>I won't have</i> <i>
to take care of her.</i>

22:05.324 --> 22:09.589
Liza, dear child,
I have a gift for you.

22:09.632 --> 22:12.722
[panting, whimpers]

22:12.766 --> 22:14.245
Mm-hmm.

22:14.289 --> 22:15.464
A dog?

22:15.508 --> 22:17.466
What am I supposed
to do with that thing?

22:17.510 --> 22:19.338
You know mom's allergic.

22:23.603 --> 22:26.475
<i>This will be more difficult</i> <i>
than I first thought.</i>

22:26.519 --> 22:28.042
[liquid splashing]

22:28.085 --> 22:32.046
<i>[McElroy Bros.'</i> <i>
"Can't You See My Smilin'"]</i>

22:32.089 --> 22:36.050
<i>♪ Can't you see</i> <i>
me smiling, baby? ♪</i>

22:36.093 --> 22:40.228
<i>♪ Can't you see</i> <i>
this face of mine? ♪</i>

22:40.271 --> 22:43.492
<i>♪ Can't you see</i> <i>
I'm getting tired? ♪</i>

22:43.536 --> 22:46.669
<i>♪ Even though</i> <i>
I seem all right ♪</i>

22:46.713 --> 22:49.063
<i>♪</i>

22:49.106 --> 22:52.240
<i>♪ It's not my life</i> <i>
I'm worried about ♪</i>

22:52.283 --> 22:56.592
<i>♪ Or my health,</i> <i>
if it's weak or strong ♪</i>

22:56.636 --> 23:00.509
<i>♪ Ooh, it's just</i> <i>
who I need, girl ♪</i>

23:00.553 --> 23:02.032
Ew.

23:02.076 --> 23:05.035
<i>♪ And who I hurt</i>

23:05.079 --> 23:07.647
<i>♪ Go on by</i>

23:07.690 --> 23:10.214
No, there's a--

23:10.258 --> 23:11.520
You--

23:11.564 --> 23:13.957
Got the balloon arch going.

23:14.001 --> 23:17.178
This guy, old prospector--
looking great, everyone.

23:17.221 --> 23:19.049
- Hi, Kayla.
- Hey, Kate.

23:19.093 --> 23:21.312
Uh, isn't the booth
supposed to be

23:21.356 --> 23:23.706
just back a couple feet?
- Yeah, there was a rock there.

23:23.750 --> 23:27.362
See, all the booths are
supposed to be 30 feet apart.

23:27.406 --> 23:29.146
Did you know that
the human brain

23:29.190 --> 23:31.235
gets pleasure from symmetry?

23:31.279 --> 23:33.237
Did you know
that the human ankle gets pain

23:33.281 --> 23:35.805
from breaking itself
on a rock?

23:35.849 --> 23:37.677
Oh, no.

23:37.720 --> 23:39.592
Why is there a murderer here?

23:39.635 --> 23:42.072
- Innocent until proven guilty.
- Innocent?

23:42.116 --> 23:43.465
[whispering]
She's holding a weapon.

23:43.509 --> 23:46.555
- Honey, it's a paintbrush.
- That's a weapon.

23:46.599 --> 23:48.905
"Hi. What would you like me
to paint on your face--

23:48.949 --> 23:50.429
a nice little birdie?"

23:50.472 --> 23:52.213
[grunts]
"Take that kid."

23:52.256 --> 23:54.868
[grunting]

23:54.911 --> 23:57.000
Keep an eye on her.

23:59.263 --> 24:00.830
It's good to see you.

24:02.528 --> 24:04.791
<i>- This is stupid.</i> <i>
- It is not stupid.</i>

24:04.834 --> 24:06.749
This is Patience Family Day.

24:06.793 --> 24:08.316
We are a family in Patience,

24:08.359 --> 24:11.624
and this is what families
in Patience do on this day.

24:11.667 --> 24:13.669
<i>If she were home with me</i> <i>
for one more second,</i>

24:13.713 --> 24:16.759
<i>I would kill her and feed her</i> <i>
to my hungry octopus.</i>

24:16.803 --> 24:18.021
Can I at least drive?

24:18.065 --> 24:21.721
- Will you stop complaining?
- Yes.

24:21.764 --> 24:23.940
- Okay.
- Yes!

24:23.984 --> 24:26.900
<i>[quirky whistling music]</i>

24:26.943 --> 24:32.688
<i>♪</i>

24:32.732 --> 24:34.603
Hurry.

24:34.647 --> 24:36.039
Okay.

24:36.083 --> 24:40.957
<i>♪</i>

24:41.001 --> 24:43.960
Okay.
Try not to kill us.

24:44.004 --> 24:45.658
Calm down.
It's fine.

24:45.701 --> 24:47.268
<i>This is a nightmare.</i>

24:47.311 --> 24:49.792
<i>How do human parents teach</i> <i>
driving to their children</i>

24:49.836 --> 24:51.315
<i>without being terrified?</i>

24:51.359 --> 24:54.188
The truck sounds like
it wants you to shift now.

24:56.146 --> 24:58.845
Oh, let's put on some tunes.

24:58.888 --> 25:01.804
Wait, watch out!
[horn blaring]

25:01.848 --> 25:05.634
- Stop being a backseat driver.
- There is no back seat.

25:05.678 --> 25:07.810
It is a truck.

25:07.854 --> 25:11.074
It is a nice day, and...

25:11.118 --> 25:12.859
that is a beautiful stop sign approaching.

25:12.902 --> 25:14.513
You see it?
- Where?

25:14.556 --> 25:15.775
There. [groans]

25:15.818 --> 25:16.993
[horn honking,
tires screeching]

25:17.037 --> 25:18.212
Watch it, asshole!

25:18.255 --> 25:20.519
Stop! That's it!
Get out of that truck!

25:20.562 --> 25:22.608
You are the worst driver
I've ever seen!

25:22.651 --> 25:26.133
You're a jerk.
I was finally having some fun.

25:30.616 --> 25:32.574
Damn it.

25:34.315 --> 25:36.491
Come on, we got to hurry.
We'll be late for the play.

25:36.535 --> 25:38.145
I don't want to give
the ball back.

25:38.188 --> 25:39.973
We have no choice.

25:40.016 --> 25:41.365
Do you know what
a kidnapping review

25:41.409 --> 25:43.585
will do to my whole
dog-walking business?

25:45.587 --> 25:46.936
Wait.

25:46.980 --> 25:49.591
Someone's been here.
The satellite dish is gone.

25:51.724 --> 25:53.726
Oh, no.

25:53.769 --> 25:56.729
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

25:56.772 --> 26:02.691
<i>♪</i>

26:02.735 --> 26:04.301
The ball.

26:06.608 --> 26:08.741
Who took it?

26:08.784 --> 26:10.960
There's only one possibility.

26:11.004 --> 26:18.098
<i>♪</i>

26:19.926 --> 26:21.884
[light clatter outside]

26:21.928 --> 26:24.887
[metallic whooshing]

26:24.931 --> 26:32.068
<i>♪</i>

26:36.638 --> 26:39.598
[indistinct excited chatter]

26:42.862 --> 26:44.341
Asta.

26:44.385 --> 26:45.865
Hey, Harry.

26:45.908 --> 26:48.215
Thank you so much again for
helping Sunny with her baby.

26:48.258 --> 26:49.477
You were amazing.

26:49.520 --> 26:51.348
They are easy
when they are babies.

26:51.392 --> 26:52.698
