30:37.661 --> 30:38.924
I'm an adult.

30:38.967 --> 30:42.014
- Shut up. No, you're not.
- Okay.

30:42.057 --> 30:43.189
Will all remaining entrants

30:43.232 --> 30:44.843
please make their way
to the table?

30:44.886 --> 30:47.410
Let's get started.
- Whoo! Let's go, D'arce!

30:47.454 --> 30:49.543
I've been practicing
with, like, hot things--

30:49.586 --> 30:53.286
like, getting, like,
big, hot things in my mouth.

30:53.329 --> 30:55.592
I mean, this is
the first time its pepper.

30:55.636 --> 30:57.899
Okay, we are
just about to start.

30:57.943 --> 31:01.207
- What are you doing?
- What? I love spicy food.

31:01.250 --> 31:02.861
This isn't spicy food.

31:02.904 --> 31:04.688
This is the stuff they put
a tiny bit of in

31:04.732 --> 31:06.386
to make spicy food.

31:06.429 --> 31:09.302
- Afraid I'm going to beat you?
- I'm afraid you're gonna die.

31:09.345 --> 31:11.217
You're going down
this year, skank.

31:11.260 --> 31:13.741
- Not as often as you.
- True, true.

31:13.784 --> 31:16.483
First up
is a very mild banana pepper.

31:16.526 --> 31:20.400
Eat!
[cheers and applause]

31:20.443 --> 31:24.534
<i>[quirky music]</i>

31:24.578 --> 31:27.581
[shouting]
I'm on fire!

31:27.624 --> 31:31.237
Nope, nope, nope, I'm out!
I'm out!

31:31.280 --> 31:33.848
Ow. No, no, no.

31:33.892 --> 31:35.937
[cheers and applause continue]

31:35.981 --> 31:38.113
Oh, hey, Doc, um...

31:38.157 --> 31:40.942
can I talk to you in private
for a minute?

31:40.986 --> 31:42.552
Nice alien.

31:42.596 --> 31:44.163
Thanks.
My dad stole it for me.

31:44.206 --> 31:47.209
Oh, that--
that's a little bit illegal.

31:47.253 --> 31:49.037
It's, like,
super cheap, so...

31:49.081 --> 31:50.996
Yeah, doesn't really--
it's more the principle.

31:51.039 --> 31:53.041
- Okay.
- Here.

31:55.174 --> 31:57.480
Look, uh,
I'll make this quick.

31:57.524 --> 32:01.397
All right, um, two weeks ago,
I took my dad to get a biopsy,

32:01.441 --> 32:03.356
except I don't remember
taking him.

32:03.399 --> 32:05.053
I don't remember anything--
as a matter of fact,

32:05.097 --> 32:06.750
I don't remember anything
about that day at all

32:06.794 --> 32:08.535
except talking to the FBI.

32:08.578 --> 32:09.971
That's not normal, right?

32:10.015 --> 32:12.191
<i>He is right.</i> <i>
It is not normal.</i>

32:12.234 --> 32:14.106
<i>And it is also very bad</i> <i>
for me.</i>

32:14.149 --> 32:16.064
All right, now get this--
it gets weirder, right?

32:16.108 --> 32:17.370
Now, I haven't told Deputy Liv

32:17.413 --> 32:18.937
anything about me
forgetting that day

32:18.980 --> 32:20.068
'cause I don't want her
to freak out,

32:20.112 --> 32:21.722
but she's got gaps
in her memory

32:21.765 --> 32:23.245
for that exact same day, too.

32:23.289 --> 32:25.944
You think if I came by office,
you could check me out?

32:25.987 --> 32:27.206
<i>This is bad.</i>

32:27.249 --> 32:28.947
<i>If he starts</i> <i>
investigating this,</i>

32:28.990 --> 32:30.861
<i>he might remember</i> <i>
that I'm a murderer</i>

32:30.905 --> 32:32.515
<i>and possibly a werewolf.</i>

32:32.559 --> 32:33.995
Yes.

32:34.039 --> 32:36.389
I will do what I can to help
with your memory.

32:36.432 --> 32:37.868
I appreciate it.

32:37.912 --> 32:40.436
You know, my dad--he tells me
it's emotional, right?

32:40.480 --> 32:42.438
That it's in my head.

32:42.482 --> 32:45.267
I lost a friend
a few years back, and...

32:45.311 --> 32:48.053
truth is, I don't think
I've had a good day since.

32:48.096 --> 32:49.750
Does that make sense?

32:49.793 --> 32:51.926
Yes, that makes sense.

32:51.970 --> 32:55.060
All I got left now
is my dad, and...

32:55.103 --> 32:57.149
who knows for how long, right?

32:57.192 --> 33:00.065
If I can't remember the time
I'm spending with him, then...

33:00.108 --> 33:02.676
- Sit down.
- Right here?

33:02.719 --> 33:04.504
- Mm.
- Okay.

33:06.810 --> 33:09.552
Let me lead you
through a meditation

33:09.596 --> 33:11.815
that will help with your grief.
- Okay.

33:11.859 --> 33:13.600
<i>And put a memory</i> <i>
in your head</i>

33:13.643 --> 33:14.949
<i>so you leave me alone.</i>

33:14.993 --> 33:16.124
All right.

33:16.168 --> 33:19.301
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

33:19.345 --> 33:21.260
<i>♪</i>

33:21.303 --> 33:23.305
We are getting up there now.

33:23.349 --> 33:28.049
Next is the Trinidad Scorpion
at 1.2 million Scoville units.

33:28.093 --> 33:30.443
This is gonna turn out bad.

33:30.486 --> 33:33.011
Why are you doing this?
Take your milk.

33:33.054 --> 33:34.273
I feel great.

33:34.316 --> 33:37.537
All right, D'arcy!
You can do this, Asta!

33:40.279 --> 33:42.542
Whoo, Asta! Yes.

33:44.109 --> 33:45.762
Mm-mm.
[coughs]

33:45.806 --> 33:47.851
Oh, God, that's not the way
you're supposed to eat that.

33:47.895 --> 33:49.810
- I'm fine, I'm fine.
- No, you're not.

33:49.853 --> 33:51.681
You're not gonna be fine.
- Oh, God.

33:51.725 --> 33:52.813
[coughing]

33:52.856 --> 33:55.903
- All right.
- [groaning]

33:55.946 --> 33:58.993
- I'm out, I'm out, I'm out.
- [coughing]

33:59.037 --> 34:01.300
And the winner
and new champion is

34:01.343 --> 34:02.692
Ellen Cho!

34:02.736 --> 34:07.567
[cheers and applause]

34:07.610 --> 34:10.526
Bow to me!
Bow!

34:10.570 --> 34:12.572
The play's about to start.
I saved you guys some seats.

34:12.615 --> 34:14.835
- Oh, I'm excited.
- I don't do no plays.

34:14.878 --> 34:16.184
I don't play.
I don't watch plays.

34:16.228 --> 34:17.838
I don't want--I ain't want
to do no plays.

34:17.881 --> 34:19.448
Oh, come on,
come on, come on.

34:19.492 --> 34:21.015
Come on, let's go.

34:21.059 --> 34:22.538
- Did you write it?
- I did.

34:22.582 --> 34:24.888
Wow, a pickax
for my tenth birthday?

34:24.932 --> 34:26.107
Thanks, Dad!

34:26.151 --> 34:28.631
all: We're all miners now.

34:28.675 --> 34:31.069
Mining built the town
of Patience, Colorado.

34:31.112 --> 34:33.027
At one time,
every able-bodied man

34:33.071 --> 34:35.682
who lived here
worked the mine.

34:35.725 --> 34:38.946
Then one cold January day
in 1884,

34:38.989 --> 34:40.861
heroes were born.

34:40.904 --> 34:42.471
[ragtime music plays, crashing]

34:42.515 --> 34:43.820
[all gasping]

34:43.864 --> 34:46.345
Oh, no!
It could be a cave-in!

34:46.388 --> 34:50.697
Run for your lives!
[all screaming]

34:50.740 --> 34:52.394
Help! Help!

34:52.438 --> 34:54.048
There's one man
still in the mine!

34:54.092 --> 34:56.355
We must go back for him!

34:56.398 --> 34:59.706
59 brave men refused
to leave one man behind.

34:59.749 --> 35:01.577
They were heroes.

35:01.621 --> 35:04.363
How much of the town budget
did you spend on this play?

35:04.406 --> 35:06.800
- Eight percent.
- Eight perc--

35:06.843 --> 35:08.236
[scoffs]

35:08.280 --> 35:11.370
What happened in the mine
after it collapsed.

35:13.154 --> 35:15.722
We're boulders,
and we're here to kill miners.

35:15.765 --> 35:18.159
All must die.

35:18.203 --> 35:21.075
[all screaming]

35:21.119 --> 35:24.034
<i>[tragic music]</i>

35:24.078 --> 35:31.172
<i>♪</i>

35:47.188 --> 35:49.625
All my organs
are hemorrhaging.

35:49.669 --> 35:51.758
[both laughing]

35:51.801 --> 35:54.239
My leg, my leg.

35:54.282 --> 35:57.590
59 men succumbed to
their crush injuries that day.

35:57.633 --> 36:00.767
And one man, who was trapped
in an air pocket,

36:00.810 --> 36:04.292
died of loneliness and thirst
three days later.

36:04.336 --> 36:08.340
I'm so thirsty and so lonely.

36:08.383 --> 36:09.993
[grunts]

36:10.037 --> 36:13.258
To the 59
and to Air Pocket Pete.

36:13.301 --> 36:15.564
I don't think his name
was actually Pete,

36:15.608 --> 36:18.611
but, you know, it works,
and it works well.

36:18.654 --> 36:20.308
[light music playing]

36:20.352 --> 36:24.443
♪ Where have all
the daddies gone? ♪

36:24.486 --> 36:28.795
♪ Where did they all go?
[both snickering]

36:28.838 --> 36:33.278
♪ My uncle is my daddy now

36:33.321 --> 36:37.847
♪ And soon there will be snow

36:37.891 --> 36:42.156
♪ Where did Mommy's happy go?

36:42.200 --> 36:46.116
♪ She drinks wine all day

36:46.160 --> 36:50.643
